{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01Q6sLeV67Nctk6QUvTBUyh7","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Given the large number of files, I'll summarize the key components:\n\nDetailed Project Structure:\n1. Project Type: Quarkus-based Coffee Shop Application\n2. Main Technologies:\n   - Quarkus Framework\n   - PostgreSQL Database\n   - Kafka (via Redpanda)\n   - Maven Build System\n\nKey Project Components:\n1. Domains:\n   - Counter (order processing)\n   - Barista (coffee preparation)\n   - Kitchen (food preparation)\n   - Core domain objects (Order, LineItem, etc.)\n\n2. Architectural Patterns:\n   - Event-driven architecture\n   - Microservices-like separation of concerns\n   - Domain-driven design with value objects and commands\n\n3. Database Configuration:\n   - Multiple schema-based datasources (coffeeshop, barista, kitchen)\n   - Supports dev (H2), test (PostgreSQL), and prod environments\n\n4. Deployment:\n   - Docker Compose setup with:\n     - PostgreSQL database\n     - Redpanda (Kafka-like) messaging\n     - pgAdmin (optional)\n     - Quarkus application\n\n5. Web Resources:\n   - Bootstrap-based frontend\n   - Custom CSS and JavaScript\n   - Responsive design\n   - Dashboard and API endpoints\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of the project or dive deeper into any particular component?"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"243793b8-1f2f-4a19-bc0b-f6e1ac6e38fc","uuid":"9751e13a-15f6-42ad-90d5-0008bea5fb5d"}
