{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01TGZE4hFjcgjzmbFmNFFnFS","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→package io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.infrastructure;\n     2→\n     3→import io.quarkuscoffeeshop.coffeeshop.counter.api.OrderService;\n     4→import org.slf4j.Logger;\n     5→import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;\n     6→import org.springframework.stereotype.Component;\n     7→\n     8→import jakarta.annotation.PostConstruct;\n     9→\n    10→/**\n    11→ * Connects the EventBusService orders-up channel to the OrderService\n    12→ */\n    13→@Component\n    14→public class OrdersUpListener {\n    15→\n    16→    private static final Logger LOGGER = LoggerFactory.getLogger(OrdersUpListener.class);\n    17→\n    18→    private final EventBusService eventBusService;\n    19→    private final OrderService orderService;\n    20→\n    21→    public OrdersUpListener(EventBusService eventBusService, OrderService orderService) {\n    22→        this.eventBusService = eventBusService;\n    23→        this.orderService = orderService;\n    24→    }\n    25→\n    26→    @PostConstruct\n    27→    public void init() {\n    28→        eventBusService.registerOrdersUpHandler(json -> {\n    29→            LOGGER.debug(\"OrderUp received, forwarding to OrderService: {}\", json);\n    30→            orderService.onOrderUp(json);\n    31→        });\n    32→    }\n    33→}\n    34→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_017q7gW47eNqthNXmFskqhJa","session_id":"243793b8-1f2f-4a19-bc0b-f6e1ac6e38fc","uuid":"5beeeaeb-7fbd-493f-b0e2-95f551ff5afd"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_bdrk_01ScKbT4Ld97PgcChx2u5Ugd","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! All four files have been successfully written. Let me provide a summary of the changes:\n\n## Successfully Written Files\n\nAll four Java entity files have been refactored for the Quarkus-to-Spring-Boot migration:\n\n### 1. **Order.java** \nPath: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/domain/Order.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Removed `extends PanacheEntityBase`\n- Removed `io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntityBase` import\n- Removed `io.smallrye.mutiny.Uni` import and the `fromAsync()` method\n- Kept the custom String ID (`orderId`) as-is since it's manually set\n- Cleaned up extra logging and comments\n\n### 2. **LineItem.java**\nPath: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/domain/LineItem.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Removed `extends PanacheEntityBase`\n- Removed `io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntityBase` import\n- Kept the custom String ID (`itemId`) generated via UUID in the constructor\n\n### 3. **BaristaItem.java**\nPath: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/barista/domain/BaristaItem.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Removed `extends PanacheEntity`\n- Removed `io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity` import\n- Added explicit `@Id` with `@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)` for auto-generated Long ID\n- Added getter/setter methods for the `id` field\n- Removed schema specification from `@Table` annotation (changed from `@Table(name = \"barista_order\", schema = \"barista\")` to `@Table(name = \"barista_order\")`)\n\n### 4. **KitchenOrder.java**\nPath: `/home/bmcginn/git/scarf-latest/scarbench-evals/final/prompt_claude__whole_applications__coffee-shop__quarkus__spring/run_1/output/src/main/java/io/quarkuscoffeeshop/coffeeshop/kitchen/domain/KitchenOrder.java`\n\n**Key Changes:**\n- Removed `extends PanacheEntity`\n- Removed `io.quarkus.hibernate.orm.panache.PanacheEntity` import\n- Added explicit `@Id` with `@GeneratedValue(strategy = GenerationType.IDENTITY)` for auto-generated Long ID\n- Added getter/setter methods for the `id` field\n- Removed schema specification from `@Table` annotation (changed from `@Table(name = \"kitchen_order\", schema = \"kitchen\")` to `@Table(name = \"kitchen_order\")`)\n\nAll files now use standard JPA annotations and are compatible with Spring Boot's JPA implementation. The entities that previously extended `PanacheEntity` now have explicit ID fields with appropriate generation strategies, while those that had custom IDs (Order and LineItem) maintain their original ID management approach."}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"243793b8-1f2f-4a19-bc0b-f6e1ac6e38fc","uuid":"c62f3de1-849e-471c-b274-529c83b54af4"}
